{"word":"πολέω","slug":"πολέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πολέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πέλω'><el>πέλω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πολέω'><el>πολέω</el></a> like <a href='S:πολεύω'><el>πολεύω</el></a>, only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to go about, range over</i>, <el>νῆσον Αἴαντος πολεῖ</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>τί σὺ τῆιδε πολεῖς</el>; <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to turn up</i> the earth with the plough, <i>to plough</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}